      • How important is build quality and material?
        The durability and feel of a keyboard can greatly affect user experience. Keyboards with a metal frame and high-quality plastic keycaps tend to last longer and feel more stable. If longevity and a solid typing experience are important, prioritize keyboards with robust build quality.
